<topic id="editingActions">
  <title>Toolbar, Contextual Menu, and Shortcut Actions</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Editing actions</indexterm>
        <indexterm>Toolbar actions</indexterm>
        <indexterm>Contextual menu actions</indexterm>
        <indexterm>Shortcuts</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p id="p_ir4_dgk_54b"><ph keyref="webappProduct"/> includes a variety of editing actions that are available on the
      toolbar and from the contextual menu (on desktop devices).</p>
    <section id="review_actions_toolbar">
      <title>Review Actions Toolbar</title>
      <p id="p_jr4_dgk_54b">The <uicontrol>Review</uicontrol> toolbar contains actions to assist you with review tasks.
        On a desktop device, some of these actions are also available in the contextual menu.</p>
      <p id="p_kr4_dgk_54b">
        <fig id="fig_lr4_dgk_54b">
          <title>Review Actions</title>
          <image href="../img/WA_review_toolbar.png"/>
        </fig>
      </p>
      <p id="p_mr4_dgk_54b">The actions include:<dl id="dl_nr4_dgk_54b">
          <dlentry id="dlentry_or4_dgk_54b">
            <dt><uicontrol><image href="../img/TrackChanges20.png" id="image_tqd_n1g_wr"/>Toggle
                Change Tracking</uicontrol></dt>
            <dd>Toggles <term>Change Tracking</term> mode on or off.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-webapp/accept-changes" id="dlentry_pr4_dgk_54b">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-webapp/reject-changes" id="dlentry_qr4_dgk_54b">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-webapp/add-comment" id="dlentry_rr4_dgk_54b">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-webapp/edit-comment" id="dlentry_sr4_dgk_54b">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-webapp/remove-comment" id="dlentry_tr4_dgk_54b">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="dlentry_ur4_dgk_54b">
            <dt><uicontrol><image href="../img/WebAuthorPrevious16.png"/>Previous
              Marker</uicontrol></dt>
            <dd>Navigates to the previous change or comment.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="dlentry_vr4_dgk_54b">
            <dt><uicontrol><image href="../img/WebAuthorNext16.png"/>Next Marker</uicontrol></dt>
            <dd>Navigates to the next change or comment.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="dlentry_wr4_dgk_54b">
            <dt><uicontrol><image href="../img/TrackChangesViewDrop.png"/>Track Changes
                Visualization Modes</uicontrol> Drop-down Menu</dt>
            <dd>This drop-down menu includes specialized actions that allow you to switch between
              the following visualization modes for the <term>Track Changes</term> feature:<ul id="ul_xr4_dgk_54b">
                <li id="li_yr4_dgk_54b"><uicontrol><image href="../img/TrackChangesFinalWithChanges16.gif"
                      id="image_why_x4v_5r"/>View All Changes/Comments</uicontrol> - This mode is
                  active by default. When you use this mode, all tracked changes are
                  represented.</li>
                <li id="li_zr4_dgk_54b"><uicontrol><image href="../img/TrackChangesFinal16.gif" id="image_zvl_y4v_5r"
                    />View Final</uicontrol> - This mode offers a preview of the document as if all
                  tracked changes (both inserted and deleted) were accepted.</li>
                <li id="li_as4_dgk_54b"><uicontrol><image href="../img/TrackChangesOriginal16.gif" id="image_kqc_z4v_5r"
                    />View Original</uicontrol> - This mode offers a preview of the document as if
                  all tracked changes (both inserted and deleted) were rejected. If you attempt to
                  edit the document in this mode, the view mode will switch to <uicontrol>View All
                    Changes/Comments</uicontrol>.</li>
              </ul></dd>
          </dlentry>
        </dl></p>
    </section>
    <section id="frameworkspecific_actions_desktop_version">
      <title>Framework-Specific Actions Toolbar</title>
      <p id="p_bs4_dgk_54b">Depending on the type of document you are editing, the toolbar and contextual menu contains
        a series of actions defined at <term>framework</term> level. <ph keyref="webappProduct"/>
        includes built-in actions for DITA, DITA Map, DocBook, TEI, and XHTML document types. On a
        desktop device, many of these actions are also available in the contextual menu. <i><i>On
            mobile devices, the framework-specific toolbar is only available in Edit mode
          </i></i>(<image href="../img/WA_Edit_Mode20.png"/>).</p>
      <p id="p_cs4_dgk_54b">
        <fig id="fig_ds4_dgk_54b">
          <title>Example: DITA Toolbar</title>
          <image href="../img/WA_DITA_toolbar.png"/>
        </fig>
      </p>
      <p id="p_es4_dgk_54b">The actions include:<dl id="dl_fs4_dgk_54b">
          <dlentry id="IX-Styling_actions">
            <dt>Styling actions</dt>
            <dd>Most common styling actions, such as <uicontrol>Bold</uicontrol>,
                <uicontrol>Italic</uicontrol>, <uicontrol>Underline</uicontrol>.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="dlentry_gs4_dgk_54b">
            <dt>Insert actions</dt>
            <dd>Actions for inserting a variety of <term>framework</term>-specific objects, such as
              images, equations, tables, paragraphs, links (for example, cross references, file
              references, or web links in DITA), topic references (<term>DITA map</term>), reusable
              content references (DITA), relationship tables (<term>DITA map</term>), and
              others.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="IX-List_actions">
            <dt>List actions</dt>
            <dd>Actions that allow you to create ordered and unordered lists, and add new items in
              them. These list buttons can also be used to convert an existing list to another type
              (for example, an unordered list to an ordered list) or to convert the current
              paragraph to a list.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="IX-Table_actions">
            <dt>Table actions</dt>
            <dd>Actions that allow you to create a table and manage its structure (insert and delete
              rows and columns).</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-webapp/IX-Insert_special_char" id="IX-Insert_special_char">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
        </dl></p>
      <p id="p_hs4_dgk_54b">For a complete list of toolbar actions for DITA Topic document types, see <xref
          href="WA-dita-topic-doc-type.dita#WA-dita-topic-doc-type/dita-toolbar-actions-section"
        />.</p>
    </section>
    <section id="contextual_menu_actions_desktop_version">
      <title>Contextual Menu Actions (Desktop Devices)</title>
      <p id="p_is4_dgk_54b">In a desktop web browser, the contextual menu also offers numerous
        editing actions, along with <term>framework</term>-specific actions. For a complete list of
        actions available for DITA documents, see <xref
          href="WA-dita-topic-doc-type.dita#WA-dita-topic-doc-type/dita_contextual_menu_actions"/>
        or <xref href="WA-dita-map-doc-type.dita#WA-dita-map-doc-type/dita_contextual_menu_actions"
        />.</p>
      <p id="p_bdm_ylk_qqb">The contextual menu includes the following actions:<dl
          id="dl_js4_dgk_54b">
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-webapp/accept-changes" id="dlentry_os4_dgk_54b">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-webapp/reject-changes" id="dlentry_ps4_dgk_54b">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-webapp/add-comment" id="dlentry_ks4_dgk_54b">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="reply-to-comments">
            <dt><uicontrol><image href="../img/ReplyBlue16.png"/>Reply</uicontrol> (Available when
              invoked on a comment or change)</dt>
            <dd>Opens a dialog box that allows you to add a reply to a comment or tracked change.
              After a reply is added, it is displayed with an indentation in the tooltip when
              hovering over the comment or change, and in the <uicontrol>Review</uicontrol>
              view.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-webapp/edit-comment" id="dlentry_ls4_dgk_54b">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-webapp/remove-comment" id="dlentry_ms4_dgk_54b">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-webapp/edit-attributes" id="dlentry_ns4_dgk_54b">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
        <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-webapp/edit-profiling-attributes">
          <dt/>
          <dd/>
        </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-webapp/surround-with" id="dlentry_qs4_dgk_54b">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="dlentry_rs4_dgk_54b">
            <dt><uicontrol>Insert</uicontrol> Submenu</dt>
            <dd>Provides various <term>framework</term>-specific actions for inserting a variety of
              objects, such as <uicontrol><image href="../img/Table16.png"/>Insert
              Table</uicontrol>, <uicontrol><image href="../img/Image16.gif" id="image_lqj_f1z_tr"
                />Insert Image</uicontrol>, <uicontrol><image href="../img/Equation16.gif"/>Insert
                Equation</uicontrol> (for <xref
                href="performing-common-actions.dita#performing-common-actions/editing_mathml_equations"
                >inserting MathML equations</xref>), <uicontrol><image
                  href="../img/InsertElement16.png"/>Insert Element</uicontrol>, and more.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="dlentry_znw_3ps_4qb">
            <dt><uicontrol>Style</uicontrol> Submenu</dt>
            <dd>Provides various <term>framework</term>-specific styling actions, such as
                  <uicontrol><image href="../img/Bold16.gif"/>Bold</uicontrol>, <uicontrol><image
                  href="../img/Italic16.png"/>Italic</uicontrol>, <uicontrol><image
                  href="../img/Underline16.gif"/>Underline</uicontrol>, <uicontrol><image
                  href="../img/Subscript16.png"/>Subscript</uicontrol>, <uicontrol><image
                  href="../img/Superscript16.png"/>Superscript</uicontrol>, and more.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="dlentry_rg4_dgk_54b">
            <dt><uicontrol>Section</uicontrol> Submenu (DocBook)</dt>
            <dd>Includes actions for promoting or demoting sections.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="dlentry_t3c_jss_4qb">
            <dt><uicontrol>Link</uicontrol> Submenu</dt>
            <dd>Provides various <term>framework</term>-specific actions for inserting types of
              links (e.g. <uicontrol>Cross Reference</uicontrol>, <uicontrol>File
                Reference</uicontrol>, <uicontrol>Web Link</uicontrol>).</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="dlentry_clw_wvn_s5b">
            <dt><uicontrol>Select</uicontrol> Submenu</dt>
            <dd>Includes actions for selecting an <uicontrol>Element</uicontrol>, its
                <uicontrol>Content</uicontrol>, or its <uicontrol>Parent</uicontrol> element.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="dlentry_h15_vss_4qb">
            <dt><uicontrol>Generate IDs</uicontrol> (DITA, DocBook, TEI)</dt>
            <dd>
              <p id="p_i15_vss_4qb"><term>Oxygen</term> generates unique IDs for the current element
                (or elements), depending on how the action is invoked:<ul id="ul_j15_vss_4qb">
                  <li id="li_k15_vss_4qb">When invoked on a single selection, an ID is generated for
                    the selected element at the cursor position.</li>
                  <li id="li_l15_vss_4qb">When invoked on a block of selected content, IDs are
                    generated for all top-level elements and elements from the list in the
                      <uicontrol>ID Options</uicontrol> dialog box found in the current
                    selection.</li>
                </ul><note id="note_m15_vss_4qb">The <uicontrol>Generate IDs</uicontrol> action does
                  not overwrite existing ID values. It only affects elements that do not already
                  have an <xmlatt>id</xmlatt> attribute.</note></p>
            </dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="dlentry_ihq_xss_4qb">
            <dt><uicontrol>Reuse</uicontrol> Submenu (DITA)</dt>
            <dd>Provides various DITA-specific actions for reusing content.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="dlentry_ss4_dgk_54b">
            <dt><uicontrol><image href="../img/Cut16.png"/>Cut</uicontrol> (<uicontrol
                conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_x"/>)</dt>
            <dd>Removes the selected content and copies it to the clipboard. You can then use the
                <uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_v"/> keyboard shortcut to
              paste the content (or use the <uicontrol><image href="../img/Paste16.png"/>Paste
                Special</uicontrol> action from the contextual menu).</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="dlentry_ts4_dgk_54b">
            <dt><uicontrol><image href="../img/Copy16.png"/>Copy</uicontrol> (<uicontrol
                conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_c">(</uicontrol>)</dt>
            <dd>Copies the selected content to the clipboard. You can then use the <uicontrol
                conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_v"/> keyboard shortcut to paste the
              content (or use the <uicontrol><image href="../img/Paste16.png"/>Paste
                Special</uicontrol> action from the contextual menu).</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-webapp/IX-Paste_special" id="IX-Paste_special">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-webapp/folding-submenu" id="dlentry_us4_dgk_54b">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-webapp/IX-Rename_element" id="IX-Rename_element">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-webapp/delete-element" id="dlentry_vs4_dgk_54b">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="dlentry_et4_dgk_54b">
            <dt><uicontrol>About Element</uicontrol> Submenu</dt>
            <dd>
              <p id="p_erz_mbg_b1c">
                <dl id="dl_jpg_nbg_b1c">
                  <dlentry id="dlentry_kpg_nbg_b1c">
                    <dt>Browse DITA Style Guide (DITA only)</dt>
                    <dd>Opens the <b>DITA Style Guide Best Practices for Authors</b> in a preview
                      window and displays a topic that is relevant to the element at the cursor
                      position. You can use the <uicontrol>Open in new tab</uicontrol> button at the
                      bottom of the preview window to open the guide in a separate browser tab.</dd>
                  </dlentry>
                  <dlentry id="dlentry_hxn_qbg_b1c">
                    <dt>Browse Reference Manual (DITA only)</dt>
                    <dd>Opens the documentation for the current element in the Oasis reference
                      manual.</dd>
                  </dlentry>
                  <dlentry id="dlentry_ijx_5bg_b1c">
                    <dt>Inspect Styles</dt>
                    <dd>Opens the <uicontrol>CSS Inspector</uicontrol> pane that displays
                      information about the CSS styles that are applied to the currently selected
                      element.</dd>
                  </dlentry>
                </dl>
              </p>
            </dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="dlentry_ws4_dgk_54b">
            <dt>Spelling Errors</dt>
            <dd>For spelling errors, the contextual menu includes a list of suggestions that you can
              select from to replace the word and an <uicontrol>Ignore</uicontrol> option that
              instructs <ph keyref="webappProduct"/> to ignore all occurrences of that particular
              spelling error in the current document.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="dlentry_at4_dgk_54b">
            <dt>Table-Related Actions (Available when invoked on a table item)</dt>
            <dd>A variety of table editing actions are available in the contextual menu when it is
              invoked on a table (depending on the context, the table-related actions are promoted
              to the top level of the contextual menu and the <uicontrol>Other Actions</uicontrol>
              submenu provides access to the other actions).</dd>
          </dlentry>
        </dl></p>
    </section>
    <section id="section_xsb_msb_qnb">
      <title>Common Shortcut Actions</title>
      <p id="p_gt4_dgk_54b"><ph keyref="webappProduct"/> includes numerous shortcut keys that are assigned to actions
        to help you edit content.</p>
      <table frame="all" rowsep="1" colsep="1" id="table_ap1_n5b_qnb">
        <title>Frequently Used Shortcut Keys in <ph keyref="product"/></title>
        <tgroup cols="3" align="center">
          <colspec colname="newCol1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.2*"/>
          <colspec colname="c1" colnum="2" colwidth="2.75*"/>
          <colspec colname="c3" colnum="3" colwidth="3.3*" align="left"/>
          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry>Action</entry>
              <entry>Shortcut Keys</entry>
              <entry align="center">Description</entry>
            </row>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry>Beginning</entry>
              <entry><uicontrol><shortcut>Ctrl + Home</shortcut></uicontrol></entry>
              <entry>Navigates to the beginning of the document </entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Check Spelling</entry>
              <entry><uicontrol><shortcut>F7</shortcut></uicontrol></entry>
              <entry>Opens the spell checking dialog box </entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>End</entry>
              <entry><uicontrol><shortcut>Ctrl + End</shortcut></uicontrol></entry>
              <entry>Navigates to the end of the document </entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Copy</entry>
              <entry><uicontrol><shortcut>Ctrl + C</shortcut></uicontrol></entry>
              <entry>Copies selected content to the clipboard</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Cut</entry>
              <entry><uicontrol><shortcut>Ctrl + X</shortcut></uicontrol></entry>
              <entry>Cuts selected content to the clipboard</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Find</entry>
              <entry><uicontrol><shortcut>Ctrl + F</shortcut></uicontrol></entry>
              <entry>Opens Find/Replace dialog box </entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Print</entry>
              <entry><uicontrol><shortcut>Ctrl + P</shortcut></uicontrol></entry>
              <entry>Opens a Print Preview dialog box </entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Help</entry>
              <entry><uicontrol><shortcut>F1</shortcut></uicontrol></entry>
              <entry>Opens help documentation </entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Open Link</entry>
              <entry><uicontrol><shortcut>Ctrl + Click</shortcut></uicontrol> (on links)</entry>
              <entry>Opens the current link in a new browser tab</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Paste</entry>
              <entry><uicontrol><shortcut>Ctrl + V</shortcut></uicontrol></entry>
              <entry>Pastes content from the clipboard</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Redo</entry>
              <entry>
                <uicontrol><shortcut>Ctrl + Y</shortcut></uicontrol></entry>
              <entry>Re-applies the last editing action </entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Reload</entry>
              <entry><uicontrol><shortcut>F5</shortcut></uicontrol></entry>
              <entry>Reloads the current document </entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Save</entry>
              <entry><uicontrol><shortcut>Ctrl + S</shortcut></uicontrol></entry>
              <entry>Saves the current document </entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Underline</entry>
              <entry><uicontrol><shortcut>Ctrl + U</shortcut></uicontrol></entry>
              <entry>Underlines selected content</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Undo</entry>
              <entry><uicontrol><shortcut>Ctrl + Z</shortcut></uicontrol></entry>
              <entry>Reverses last editing action </entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </table>
    </section>
